factor_multiset_prod:
/-- If we start with a multiset of primes, take the product and
 then factor it, we get back the original multiset. -/
theorem factor_multiset_prod (v : prime_multiset) : v.prod.factor_multiset = v :=
  by
  apply prime_multiset.coe_nat_injective
  rw [v.prod.coe_nat_factor_multiset, prime_multiset.coe_prod]
  rcases v with ⟨l⟩
  unfold_coes
  dsimp [prime_multiset.to_nat_multiset]
  rw [Multiset.coe_prod]
  let l' := l.map (coe : Nat.Primes → ℕ)
  have : ∀ p : ℕ, p ∈ l' → p.prime := fun p hp =>
    by
    rcases list.mem_map.mp hp with ⟨⟨p', hp'⟩, ⟨h_mem, h_eq⟩⟩
    exact h_eq ▸ hp'
  exact multiset.coe_eq_coe.mpr (@nat.factors_unique _ l' rfl this).symm
#align factor_multiset_prod factor_multiset_prod

theorem factor_multiset_pow (n : «exprℕ+») (m : ℕ) : factor_multiset (n ^ m) = «expr • » m (factor_multiset n) :=
  by
  let u := factor_multiset n
  have : n = u.prod := (prod_factor_multiset n).symm
  rw [this, ← prime_multiset.prod_smul]
  repeat' rw [prime_multiset.factor_multiset_prod]
#align factor_multiset_pow factor_multiset_pow

/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«exprℕ+» -/
/-- We now have four different results that all encode the
 idea that inequality of multisets corresponds to divisibility
 of positive integers. -/
theorem factor_multiset_le_iff {m n : «exprℕ+»} : factor_multiset m ≤ factor_multiset n ↔ m ∣ n :=
  by
  constructor
  · intro h
    rw [← prod_factor_multiset m, ← prod_factor_multiset m]
    apply Dvd.intro (n.factor_multiset - m.factor_multiset).prod
    rw [← prime_multiset.prod_add, prime_multiset.factor_multiset_prod, add_tsub_cancel_of_le h, prod_factor_multiset]
  · intro h
    rw [← mul_div_exact h, factor_multiset_mul]
    exact le_self_add
#align factor_multiset_le_iff factor_multiset_le_iff
factor_multiset_lcm:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«exprℕ+» -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⊔ » -/
theorem factor_multiset_lcm (m n : «exprℕ+») :
    factor_multiset (lcm m n) = «expr ⊔ » (factor_multiset m) (factor_multiset n) :=
  by
  apply le_antisymm
  · rw [← prime_multiset.prod_dvd_iff, prod_factor_multiset]
    apply lcm_dvd <;> rw [← factor_multiset_le_iff']
    exact le_sup_left
    exact le_sup_right
  · apply sup_le_iff.mpr <;> constructor <;> apply factor_multiset_le_iff.mpr
    exact dvd_lcm_left m n
    exact dvd_lcm_right m n
#align factor_multiset_lcm factor_multiset_lcm
factor_multiset_gcd:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«exprℕ+» -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⊓ » -/
/-- The gcd and lcm operations on positive integers correspond
 to the inf and sup operations on multisets. -/
theorem factor_multiset_gcd (m n : «exprℕ+») :
    factor_multiset (gcd m n) = «expr ⊓ » (factor_multiset m) (factor_multiset n) :=
  by
  apply le_antisymm
  · apply le_inf_iff.mpr <;> constructor <;> apply factor_multiset_le_iff.mpr
    exact gcd_dvd_left m n
    exact gcd_dvd_right m n
  · rw [← prime_multiset.prod_dvd_iff, prod_factor_multiset]
    apply dvd_gcd <;> rw [prime_multiset.prod_dvd_iff']
    exact inf_le_left
    exact inf_le_right
#align factor_multiset_gcd factor_multiset_gcd

/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«exprℕ+» -/
/-- The number of occurrences of p in the factor multiset of m
 is the same as the p-adic valuation of m. -/
theorem count_factor_multiset (m : «exprℕ+») (p : Nat.Primes) (k : ℕ) :
    (p : «exprℕ+») ^ k ∣ m ↔ k ≤ m.factor_multiset.count p :=
  by
  intros
  rw [Multiset.le_count_iff_replicate_le]
  rw [← factor_multiset_le_iff, factor_multiset_pow, factor_multiset_of_prime]
  congr 2
  apply multiset.eq_replicate.mpr
  constructor
  · rw [Multiset.card_nsmul, prime_multiset.card_of_prime, mul_one]
  · intro q h
    rw [prime_multiset.of_prime, Multiset.nsmul_singleton _ k] at h
    exact Multiset.eq_of_mem_replicate h
#align count_factor_multiset count_factor_multiset
